Description: Foot sherd of Attic black-glazed pottery kylix; foot in two degrees; glazed black on top and underside; reserved: resting surface and outer face of foot; incised inscription on underside.
Bibliographic references: Petrie 1886 / Naukratis. Part I., 1884-85 (pl. XXXIV, no. 500)
Bernand 1970 / Le Delta égyptien d'après les textes grecs, i: les confins libyques (p. 675, no. 339)
Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GA.1482)
